=Pseudomonadota
gram negative

#Burkholderiales
Burkholderia pseudomallei: weaponizable
- rod shape
- causes Melioidosis: fever, pneumonia, abscesses
Burkholderia cepacia complex (BCC): antibiotic-resistant
- rod shape
- in patients with cystic fibrosis

#Hyphomicrobiales
Brucella melitensis: coccobacillus, spread by unpasteurized milk, weaponizable
- causes Brucellosis: fever, sweats, joint pain

#Thiotrichales
Francisella tularensis: coccobacillus, weaponizable
- causes Tularemia: rabbit fever
- spread by ticks

#Neisseriales
Neisseria gonorrhoeae: diplococci, sexually transmitted
- causes Gonorrhea: dysuria, inflammation, can spread to joints/heart

#Pseudomonadales
Acinetobacter baumannii
- rod shape
- in hospitals, antibiotic-resistant
Pseudomonas aeruginosa
- rod shape
- in hospitals, antibiotic-resistant
- in patients with cystic fibrosis

#Pasteurellales
Haemophilus influenzae
- round shape
- causes pneumonia and meningitis in children
- often resistant to penicillin

#Legionellales
Legionella pneumophila
- rod shape
- invades macrophages

#Enterobacterales
Escherichia coli
- rod shape
- found in lower intestines
- can cause food poisoning
Salmonella enterica
- rod shape
- food infection (egg whites)
Yersinia pestis: coccobacillus
- causes plague, spread by rat flea
Shigella
- infects colon
- causes Shigellosis: diarrhoea, fever, abdominal pain
- spread by contaminated food and water

#Vibrionales
Vibrio cholerae
- spiral shape
- causes cholera
- from contaminated shellfish or water

=Campylobacterota

#Campylobacterales
Campylobacter jejuni
- gram negative, helical shape
- food poisoning (poultry)
Helicobacter pylori
- gram negative, spiral shape
- can cause gastritis or ulcers

=Chlamydiota

#Chlamydiales
Chlamydia trachomatis
- gram negative, rod shape
- causes chlamydia
- spreads through sexual contact

=Spirochaetota

#Spirochaetales
Treponema pallidum
- gram negative, helical shape
- causes syphilis
- spreads through sexual contact
- before antibiotics treated by pyrotherapy (malaria-induced fever)

=Bacillota
gram positive

#Lactobacillales
Streptococcus pyogenes
- round shape, chains
- spreads through air droplets and skin contact
- can cause rheumatic fever
Streptococcus pneumoniae
- round shape, pairs
- spreads through air droplets
- causes pneumonia and meningitis
Streptococcus thermophilus
- round shape
- microbiota
- fermentation (milk, yogurt)
Lactobacillus acidophilus
- rod shape
- microbiota
- fermentation (milk)
Lactobacillus bulgaricus
- rod shape
- fermentation (yogurt)
Lactococcus lactis
- round shape, short chains
- fermentation (cheese)

#Bacillales
Bacillus anthracis: bioweapon
- rod shape
- causes Anthrax: skin blisters
Staphylococcus saprophyticus
- round shape
- urinary tract infection
Staphylococcus aureus
- round shape
- spreads through skin contact
- can cause skin or respiratory infection
- antibiotic-resistant strains
Listeria monocytogenes
- rod shape
- causes listeriosis
- from unpasteurized dairy

#Clostridiales
Clostridium botulinum: produces botulinum neurotoxin, lethal dose 1ng/1kg
- rod shape
- causes Botulism: weakness, trouble seeing/speaking
- from improperly canned food, from honey (infants)
Clostridium tetani: produces neurotoxin
- rod shape
- causes Tetanus
- in soil, through wound
Clostridium perfringens: tissue necrosis, gas gangrene
- rod shape
- causes food poisoning
Clostridioides difficile
- rod shape
- causes diarrhea
- spores are resistant to heat and alcohol
- fecal microbiota transplant (FMT): treatment by healthy fecal bacteria

=Actinomycetota
gram positive
genome with high GC content

#Mycobacteriales
Mycobacterium tuberculosis
- rod shape
- causes tuberculosis
- spreads through air droplets
- divides every 24h
Mycobacterium leprae
- rod shape
- causes leprosy

#Streptomycetales
Streptomyces
- produces antibiotics for drugs

#Bifidobacteriales
Bifidobacterium bifidum
- rod shape
- microbiota
